A man is tested for the novel coronavirus, COVID-19, in Vrededorp, Johannesburg, on June 5, 2020. South Africa said on June 4, 2020, it had recorded 3,267 novel coronavirus cases in 24 hours, the biggest jump since the pandemic hit the country. JOHANNESBURG - The number of positive COVID-19 cases in South Africa is 70, 038. According to the Department of Health, over 1 million tests have been conducted. There has been a further 57 COVID-19 related deaths -- 42 from Western Cape, 10 from the Eastern Cape, and 5 from KwaZulu Natal. This brings the total national deaths to 1,480. “The recoveries to date are 38 531- this translates to a recovery rate of 55%,” said the health department. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.